deck: Father of Thomas and Sela Mathers.
description:
Origin

Going by the name of Freidrich Mathers, the Trueblood Drago had two children: Thomas and Sela. After he refused to return to the Dark One's forces, his carriage, with Thomas and Sela in the back, was sabotaged. Thomas fell out immediately and Drago and Sela went over the edge. Hanging on by a rope, Drago sacrificed himself to safe Sela. He let go off the rope, so Sela could climb up safely.
name: Freidrich Mathers

deck: Advisor and son-in-law of the king and responsible for the creation of Morrigan.
description:
Origin

When the king learned of his daughter's plan to elope with the captain of the guard Morrigan, he ordered the dwarf Blagg to make Morrigan disappear. Blagg asked a fairy to kidnap Morrigan, leaving behind a 'dear John' note for Esmerelda. Approaching Esmerelda, Blagg told her he knew where Morrigan was held and helped her reach him. Upon freeing Morrigan, Blagg threw acid into Morrigan's face, scarring him. To Esmerelda Blagg said the fairy had disfigured Morrigan. Feeling Blagg had acted honorably, Esmerelda agreed to marry him.

When the king went ill not long after, the king sent for Morrigan. Returning to the kingdom, Morrigan was too late, the king had died and Blagg was now the ruler. Capturing Morrigan, Blagg sent Morrigan to prison. There, the Dark One freed Morrigan and offered him the power to take revenge on Blagg. The price was eternal service and the rest of Morrigan's humanity, turning him into Death. He immediately killed Blagg.
name: Blagg

description:
Origin

Quatro aided the prince Victor and Belinda on their quest to defeat the Wraith King. Loyal to the end, Quatro was slain by the dragon guard.
name: Quatro

description:
Origin

Prince Victor aided Belinda in her quest to defeat the Wraith King. Assisted by his loyal aide Quatro, they gained entrance to the castle, where Belinda slayed the Wraith King. Afterwards, he asked Belinda to marry him. When she was pregnant, Belinda discovered that Victor's father was working for an unnamed demon (later revealed to be Orcus) who wanted her baby as a human sacrifice. Fearing for her son, she went into labor, her son taken from her by force. Victor came to her rescue, not knowing his father's role, but was stabbed and died.
name: Victor
